# resource-monitoring-system

The resource monitoring system implements comprehensive GPU telemetry collection and alert mechanisms:

GPU Metrics Collection (Importance: 95)
- Tracks critical GPU performance indicators:
  - Utilization percentage 
  - Memory usage/allocation
  - Temperature monitoring
  - Power consumption tracking
  - Fan speeds and clock rates
  - PCIe bandwidth (RX/TX)
- Maintains 60-point sliding window history
- Default 1-second telemetry collection interval

Utilization Alert System (Importance: 85)
- GPU idle detection with configurable thresholds:
  - Default 30% utilization threshold
  - 5-minute idle time window
- Notification triggers for underutilized resources
- Thread-safe updates using RLock mechanism

Event-Driven Architecture (Importance: 90)
- Priority-based event processing system:
  - CRITICAL: Hardware safety events
  - HIGH: Resource allocation events
  - NORMAL: Standard telemetry
  - LOW: Background metrics
- Real-time metrics distribution via event bus
- Dynamic GPU detection/removal handling

